In today’s society men and women are (supposed to be) equal. Gillette’s view suggests that there is something that makes men more powerful or intelligent, such that the onus lies on men to make society more inclusive. Do you realise what message this sends? Society should be gender-neutral, but funnily enough it’s become more embroiled in gender stereotypes. 
Lastly, this whole ‘guilt by association’ campaign does little to bridge any perceived gender/ masculinity gap. When you label all members of a certain demographic as violent or vulgar, you are likely to incite more hate and increase such behaviour rather than reduce it. The future generations of that demographic have already been labelled and branded, so why not engage in more violence, crudeness, and “toxic masculinity”? You are all mistaken if you think this is about being offended.
